Module #2 // Image Generator // Extra Information ...
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Easily switch between modules by using the 1, 2, 3, & 4 number keys on your keyboard.
-------------------------------------------------------------
All modules here are uniform and have a left-to-right, top-to-bottom flow (sequential flow). Meaning they read just like a book. No nodes are hidden and all similar or branching nodes are grouped together accordingly. This aims to solve the organizational problem that most other workflows have and to simplify the creation process.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Main model used - Dreamshaper 8: 
https://civitai.com/models/4384?modelVersionId=128713
-------------------------------------------------------------
Some models download on first time use. Startup may be slow.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Experiment with different batch sizes for the "emptyimage // experimental settings" node in Text to Image for different results. The color value also has an added effect. I've also added more opitions for color modifications. This is experimental and you can bypass them if you don't like the results. 
-------------------------------------------------------------
All IPAdapter models can be found in the Comfy UI Manager Install Models tab. Type "faceid" in the search for quick picks. Update all if you run into further issues.
-------------------------------------------------------------
For SDXL & LCM simply change models and parameters to match.
-------------------------------------------------------------
All nodes are locked - to move them you will need to "unlock" them. For those who don't know the difference, locked nodes cannot be moved even with a group, while pinned nodes can still be moved with a group.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Trouble Shooting InsightFace:
If you experience this error: "No Module InsightFace"
Remove Reactor Nodes if you have them installed then manually install insightface. Follow the troubleshoot guide here:
https://github.com/Gourieff/comfyui-reactor-node#insightfacebuild

Module #2 // Image Generator // About ...
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                >>>For Image Generation<<<
-------------------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------------------
Use this to create images from text as well as loaded images. These generators aim to give you high quality outputs on queue, assuming you're using the same settings and models. Easily mute and unmute sections or groups using the fast groups muter above. Be sure to mute groups not in use!!!
-------------------------------------------------------------
Sound executes upon completion - be aware of the volume - it should be around 0.1 - which is low. (red node/playsound)
-------------------------------------------------------------
Important: Mute or bypass nodes further down the sequential line of a group to shorten generation times or to lessen v-ram usage by the generation.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Text to Image Generation: 
I use IP Adapter and connect it to a series of empty images to create an interesting effect, I find it changes the quality of the image at times. Queue will fail on MeshGraphformer - if it does not detect hands - bypass the BYPASS groups if you're not generating a human image; this will solve the error. You can also change the "mask_type" to something other than "tight boxes" if your having issues.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Image to Image Generation: 
Can also error on mesh graphormer, be sure to BYPASS when you're not creating a character with hands or change the "mask_type" to something other than "tight boxes". Also Be sure to check the github for each node to better understand what they do. Links are provided through the Comfy-UI manager.
-------------------------------------------------------------
